2 One of You Must Do This<br />
2 Trapped and Alone    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Added Gandalf to the Ranger deck to combat global conditions. Works like any other Ranger deck mostly, but without elf allies; it more relies on equipping your characters.<br />
<br />
Some I-Orc decks play lots of small minions, then drop The Trees Are Strong and sac them for more wounds. I find it more effective, however, to concentrate on winning skirmishes and getting the most out of your larger minions. Manage your minions and pumps wisely, as timing is everything and you want to have at least one threat able to wound/mess up the enemy each regroup. 18 orcs and 8 pump is a good mix for this end, but it requires that you make it count. Be very careful where you place your archery. The deck can put a hurting on any fellowship THAT GIVES ENOUGH POOL. Simply put, if your opponent all-out chokes you are screwed. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
